      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 150°C (130°C fan). Line a deep 20 cm round tin with a double layer of baking paper, extending 5 cm above the rim to protect the sides. Beat {{unsalted-butter}} and {{light-brown-sugar}} until fluffy. Beat in {{eggs}} one at a time. Fold in {{self-raising-flour}} and {{mixed-spice}}, then stir through {{sultanas}}, {{currants}}, {{mixed-peel}}, {{lemon}} zest, and {{whole-milk}}. Roll out 200 g of the {{marzipan}} to a circle just smaller than the tin. Spoon half the batter into the tin, lay the marzipan disc on top, then spoon over the remaining batter. Smooth the top. Bake for 85 to 90 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Leave to cool completely in the tin.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Decorate with marzipan",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll out 300 g of the remaining {{marzipan}} to a circle the size of the top of the cake. Brush the cooled cake with warmed {{apricot-jam}} and press the marzipan circle on top. Crimp the edge with a fork or fingers. Roll the remaining marzipan into 11 equal balls and arrange around the edge. Press down gently. Toast under a hot grill or with a kitchen torch until the marzipan is golden and lightly blistered in places.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
